---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="AI Leadership Research, Evidence, and Governance Sources | AILD"
  description="Research and evidence for AI leadership, AI governance, executive decision-making, workforce adoption, and operating model design."
  canonical="https://aild.org/research/"
  active="research"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Evidence base</p>
    <h1>Evidence base for AI governance and executive decisionmaking</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Research is the evidence layer behind AILD's frameworks. Use this page when you need external studies, standards,
      and decision science to support governance, operating model, and board-level choices.
    </p>
    <div class="badge-row">
      <span class="badge">4 evidence clusters</span>
      <span class="badge">Standards + field data + decision science</span>
      <span class="badge">Direct links to implementation guides</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section grid-2">
    <article class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Cluster 1</p>
      <h3 id="market-and-adoption">Adoption and labor dynamics</h3>
      <p>Use this cluster for workforce planning, capability development, and role redesign decisions.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.weforum.org/press/2025/01/future-of-jobs-report-2025-78-million-new-job-opportunities-by-2030-but-urgent-upskilling-needed-to-prepare-workforces/">WEF Future of Jobs 2025</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.gallup.com/workplace/699689/ai-use-at-work-rises.aspx">Gallup AI use at work (Dec 2025)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.gallup.com/workplace/701195/frequent-workplace-continued-rise.aspx">Gallup frequent use (Jan 2026)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://hai.stanford.edu/news/ai-index-2025-state-of-ai-in-10-charts">Stanford HAI AI Index 2025</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Cluster 2</p>
      <h3 id="firm-performance">Firm performance and execution</h3>
      <p>Use this cluster for investment prioritization, operating model design, and execution KPI selection.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w34836">NBER firm data on AI (w34836)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w34174">NBER retrainability (w34174)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w34705">NBER adaptability risk (w34705)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://news.microsoft.com/2024/05/08/microsoft-and-linkedin-release-the-2024-work-trend-index-on-the-state-of-ai-at-work/">Microsoft/LinkedIn Work Trend Index</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section grid-2">
    <article class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Cluster 3</p>
      <h3 id="governance-and-risk">Governance and risk controls</h3>
      <p>Use this cluster for policy design, control boundaries, and board reporting standards.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework">NIST AI Risk Management Framework</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://oecd.ai/en/ai-principles">OECD AI Principles</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/81230.html">ISO/IEC 42001 AI management systems</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://digital-strategy.ec.europa.eu/en/policies/regulatory-framework-ai">EU AI Act overview</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Cluster 4</p>
      <h3 id="decision-science">Decision science foundations</h3>
      <p>Use this cluster to improve judgment quality, meeting protocols, and executive decision cadence.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://hbr.org/2006/01/deciding-how-to-decide">HBR: Deciding How to Decide</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06747-5">Nature: Human-AI complementarity in decision tasks</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w31161">NBER: Generative AI at work and task outcomes</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.mckinsey.com/capabilities/quantumblack/our-insights/the-state-of-ai">McKinsey: The State of AI</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section panel">
    <h2 id="how-to-read-this-page">How to use this research page</h2>
    <p>
      Most AI research pages stop at citation lists. This one is meant to be operational. Use it to decide what evidence
      should inform board briefings, executive meeting protocols, AI policy design, and workflow redesign.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use adoption studies to plan capability building and role redesign</li>
      <li>Use firm-performance research to choose the right AI operating model and KPI set</li>
      <li>Use governance standards to define policy boundaries and review rules</li>
      <li>Use decision-science research to improve how leadership teams judge, escalate, and override</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="signal-note">If you want concepts, go to Learn. If you want implementation paths, go to Playbooks. If you want proof, go to Cases.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section panel">
    <h2 id="how-we-use-evidence">How AILD uses evidence</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Translate macro trends into concrete leadership operating choices</li>
      <li>Prioritize decision quality and accountability over pure output speed</li>
      <li>Combine external research with case-based implementation benchmarks</li>
      <li>Continuously update guides as evidence and tools evolve</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      For application: see <a href="/learn/">Knowledge Library</a>, <a href="/playbooks/">Playbooks</a>,
      and <a href="/cases/">Cases</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section panel">
    <h2 id="evidence-to-action-map">Evidence-to-action map</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Adoption evidence -> <a href="/learn/ai-leadership-maturity-model/">AI Leadership Maturity Model</a></li>
      <li>Risk evidence -> <a href="/learn/trust-vs-override-framework/">Trust vs Override Framework</a></li>
      <li>Execution evidence -> <a href="/learn/ai-signal-to-decision-operating-rhythm/">Signal-to-Decision Rhythm</a></li>
      <li>Board evidence -> <a href="/learn/board-ai-governance-briefing/">Board Governance Briefing</a></li>
      <li>Performance evidence -> <a href="/learn/decision-quality-scorecard-for-ai-teams/">Decision Quality Scorecard</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section panel">
    <h2 id="what-this-page-is-not">What this page is not</h2>
    <p>
      This is not a claim that one report can answer every AI strategy question. It is a curated decision-support layer.
      The goal is to help leaders connect external evidence to real operating choices instead of treating research as
      background reading only.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
